title: Neil Young Massey Hall - Toronto, ON January 12, 2014
description:
Neil Young
Massey Hall - Toronto, ON
January 12, 2014


Source: Sony HDR XR-160 > TMPGEnc V4 > BDMV
Filmer: Toronto Tapers Consortium

Ratio - 16:9
Menu - PC
Chapters - Each Song
NTSC

Video: 23 mbs 60 fps
Audio: Dolby Digital 48.0 kHz, 6 chn, 448.0 kbit/s


(1:57:27)

21) Comes A Time
22) Long May You Run



Notes:

This was filmed in super stealth mode, so that affects the quality. Notwithstanding that, it came out very well. The songs where Neil is sitting and playing guitar are excellent. Love in Mind and A Man Needs A Maid are shot from behind. Full video on those, but it's dark. The upright piano songs (AYRFTC?, Someday, Gold Rush, Journey) were tough to get. Mostly just audio, though the filmer tried to get whatever possible. The stand-up guitar songs (Changes, Needle of Death, Comes A Time, Long May You Run) are mostly pretty good. All in all, it's a nice document from this mini tour. There are some obstructions and partial obstructions throughout as people moved around. If you're a Neil fan you'll enjoy this. 

This mini tour is part of Neil's Honor The Treaties campaign. I won't share my opinion, but I encourage everyone to be educated about the issues. 

Enjoy!
